
[1]impatiently

   IMPA'TIENTLY, adv. With uneasiness or restlessness; as, to bear
   disappointment impatiently.

   1. With eager desire causing uneasiness; as, to wait impatiently for
   the arrival of one's friend.

   2. Passionately; ardently.
